# Smart Trash Bin

This project implements a smart trash bin using an ESP32 microcontroller. The trash bin features:

- Ultrasonic sensors for detecting fill level and proximity
- GPS for location tracking
- Firebase integration for storing data
- Web server for remote access
- Telegram bot for control via messages
- WiFi connectivity

## Project Structure

- `src/`: Contains all the source files for the project.
- `main.ino`: Main Arduino file.
- `*.h` and `*.cpp`: Header and source files for different functionalities.

## Getting Started

1. Clone this repository.
2. Open the project in the Arduino IDE.
3. Upload the code to your ESP32.

## Dependencies

- WiFi
- HTTPClient
- NewPing
- ESP32Servo
- TinyGPS++
- PubSubClient
- WebServer
- ArduinoJson
- UniversalTelegramBot
- FirebaseESP32

## Configuration

- Modify `secrets.h` with your Firebase credentials.
- Modify `credentials.h` with your Telegram bot token and chat ID.

## Usage

- Connect to WiFi using one of the predefined SSIDs and passwords.
- Access the web server to monitor the trash bin data.
- Send commands via Telegram to open or close the lid.
- Data is periodically sent to Firebase.

